HOW TO EXPORT MODEL FROM BLENDER TO UNITY

•	Firstly select the model/object you want to export.
•	Then go to file – export – select “.fbx”
•	A new window will get opened.
•	Now find the folder where you will export model/object.
•	There go to path mode and select copy. Also select the copy button placed right to the copy field.
•	Give name to your model/object from “untitled.fbx” to Any name.For example – “SM_platform1” , “SM_Ball”.
•	Then press export fbx button.
•	Go to folder where you export model/object.
•	Open unity and under assets folder create new folder with name Models.
•	Open this folder and drag all models into unity.
